Position: Security Guard-Commercial<br>
Job Classification: Full Time<br>
Location: Headquarters located at ADC San Mateo Office <br>
Reports To: Captain and Sergeant<br>
<br>
Summary: The Security Guard position is responsible for the protection, safeguarding, and security of assets, personnel, customers and all visitors of their assigned post.<br>
<br>
Job Responsibilities: <br>
•	Perform security patrols on premises to prevent and detect signs of intrusion and ensure security of doors, windows and gates<br>
•	Investigate and write reports on accidents, incidents, suspicious activities, safety and fire hazards and other security related situations<br>
•	Completion of Daily Activity Reports of each shift<br>
•	Answer alarms and investigate disturbances<br>
•	Prompt and timely deggy system checks<br>
•	Provide any needed assistance to customer, employees and visitors according to the site procedures<br>
•	Performs other related duties as assigned by Captain and Sergeants <br>
<br>
Qualifications:<br>
•	High school diploma or equivalent required plus any Security/Law Enforcement experience preferred. <br>
•	Must be at least 21 years of age. <br>
•	Hold and maintain Security Guard status<br>
•	Ability to perform duties in a professional manner and appearance<br>
•	Good working knowledge of security operations, safety practices in a business environment and enforcement procedures. <br>
•	Demonstrated strong English verbal and written communication skills<br>
•	Ability to understand and follow standard operating procedures<br>
•	Ability write and investigate required reports <br>
•	Ability to make independent and good judgment decisions utilizing ADC LTD NM and customer policy and procedures <br>
•	Ability to handle sensitive and confidential information<br>
<br>
Working Conditions: <br>
•	Frequent and prolonged walking, standing, sitting, and stooping, up to twelve (12) hours per day. Occasional running, sprinting, lifting heavy weights, moving heavy objects, climbing stairs<br>
•	Work is performed indoors and outdoors and require an individual to withstand extreme inclement weather such as heat, humidity, cold, or severe weather <br>
•	Unpredictable crisis situations require the ability to speak clearly and distinctly and remain calm in stressful situations <br>
•	Ability to remain on post up to four (4) consecutive hours without sitting, eating, or relieving bladder or bowels. <br>
•	Ability to remain alert with ability to mentally and physically react quickly to a variety of unexpected and dangerous situations. <br>
•	Ability to subdue violent or potentially violent or disturbed individuals, or intervene in a crisis <br>
•	Evening and Weekend Hours required    </section>

